{{Infobox organization | name = Wild Scotland | vector_logo = | type = [[Non-profit organisation]] | founded_date = 2003 | location_city = | location_country = | location = [[Inverness, Scotland]] | area_served = [[Scotland]] || homepage = [http://www.wild-scotland.co.uk Wild Scotland] | dissolved = | footnotes = }}
'''Wild Scotland''' is the Scottish Wildlife and Nature Tourism Operators Association - a not-for-profit organisation made up of wildlife and nature tourism professionals.<ref>http://www.wild-scotland.org.uk/aboutus.aspx</ref>
Formed in 2003 the association has more than 80 members which represents one quarter of Scotland's wildlife tourism businesses.<ref>https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2008/nov/30/green-travel-wildlife</ref>
